    "content": "<h1>TONGUES OF FIRE</h1><p>A phrase in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:3\">Acts 2:3</a>, describing the physical appearance of the Spirit. The tongues of fire seem to fulfill John the Baptistâ€™s prediction that the Coming One would baptize with the Holy Spirit and fire (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:11\">Matthew 3:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:16\">Luke 3:16</a>). The disciples are described as being filled with the Holy Spirit, fulfilling the Old Testament promise that John the Baptist and Jesus repeated about the baptism of the Spirit.</p><p><em>See also</em> <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"6815\" data-resourceType=\"TyndaleBibleDictionary\">Pentecost</span>.</p>",
